A composite outcome, which was also considered a determinant of treatment success, was used to determine whether an implant was successfully treated without requiring any further surgical intervention [23]. The proposed success criteria were categorized as follows:
Outcome 1: the absence of additional bone loss after the treatments according to baseline radiographs;
Outcome 2: absence of additional bone loss with a maximum PD depth of ≤ 5 mm;
Outcome 3: absence of additional bone loss with a maximum PD depth of ≤ 5 mm, and without any BOP or Supp [24].
